<br>
39 hp per tick, 10 ticks per minutes, 390 hps a minute. That is less than one half of Nature's Touch. Also, would take an average high end druid about 6 minutes to get to full from near death at this rate. Not saying it isn't nice... but I don't think the equivalent of 1 chloroblast worth of healing a minute is going to be more worthwhile than say, 100 and some extra mana. I think it is AWESOME for meleers, and shamans who can cannabalize, but like I'll say once again, if I'm getting hit, I'm probably doing something wrong as a druid. I can definately see it's uses in situations where AEs are unavoidable, but this isn't very often. So, if I had one, I would certainly keep it in my alternate gear bag and switch it in and out when necessary.<br>
<br>
On the other hand... I'm liking that Ancient Burrower Hide Tunic, we may have a new winner!<br>
<br>
Remkar<br>
